genresAdvancedInfo.name: west virginia metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: West Virginia metal is a subgenre of heavy metal that originated in the Appalachian region of the United States. It is characterized by its raw and aggressive sound, with lyrics often focusing on themes of isolation, poverty, and the struggles of rural life.
